This paper deals with bibliometric studies and the identification of excellent papers based on citation analysis. The most relevant sub-categories in arXiv CS for this topic are likely to be cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to researchers in the sub-categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as these fields often use bibliometric analysis to evaluate research impact and excellence.
